content.description:
There is really fun movement on this problem.

This is located left of

King Fin

, V4. It starts with two face holds in the overhang/cave and traverses right on to the really good flake. From the flake, there is a bit of a reach right into a face crimp. Cross into the big rail, and climb up from there. This is an eliminate boulder problem where you aren't intended to use the

King Fin

, V4 features. Using the

King Fin

, V4 features will definitely make it easier.
content.protection: 2 pads and a spotter was more than enough.
content.location:
This is on the King Fin Boulder, left of

King Fin

, V4, and it starts in the overhang.
